2.3.23

I have no desire to be with someone who completes me. I’d rather be with someone who shows me there is more to me than i even knew existed.
I’m a vibe that you’ll never forget.

So, three years ago, I opened my first brick and mortar location. Afraid is an understatement. I survived. Through a pandemic, depression, falling out of love with myself, and then back, I survived. All that to say I’m blessed. To have a company come and experience my blood sweat and tears, then leave such a radiant review is mind-blowing. To all of the support, reservations made, reposting of my store, constant encouragement, I thank you. To my family, I love you. This is ours. I reintroduce @cocoandsheaoakcliff.
Truly enjoying the fruits of my labor. God has been continuously good to me. Entering into my blessed and highly favored era.

It’s Labor Day which means fall is right around the corner . Babe wanted a drink today so I decided to whip up something smooth for him yet sexy for me, a SMOKED ROSEMARY PEACH OLD FASHIONED using @woodfordreserve. Try this recipe this holiday season , let me know what you think ! 

Recipe:
3 oz Woodford Reserve 
3 dashes of Peach Bitters 
.5 oz Peach infused simple syrup 

Stir slowly , garnish , and serve. Enjoy !
@maisonseven.us has a few releases scheduled for this fall. Myself and the team are proud of these new fragrances. Make sure to follow to stay updated throughout the season .

As many of you know I own @cocoandsheaoakcliff , a luxury home and goods store.  I’m so extremely passionate and intentional about everything I touch . I thought I would share more of myself with you all through my depictions of my simple luxuries. From libations to home decor on this side of the internet we focus on creating peace. Welcome.
"You will find that it is necessary to let things go; simply for the reason that they are heavy." — C. JoyBell

Listen , it’s 5 o’clock somewhere! I created this complex Avion de Papel  or  Anejo Paper Plane with Monday’s in mind. The flavors of this martini are robust yet smooth.  I would highly recommend you try this recipe for your next evening starter or for a fiery night cap. Either way this baby won’t miss! So put this martini on the list and prepare to take flight ! 

Drink responsibly, and Enjoy ! 

Recipe:

1 ounce Casamigos Anejo Tequila
1 ounce Aperol
¾ ounce freshly squeezed lemon juice
½ St Germain Elderflower Liqueur

*Add into a shaker with ice and shake until well-chilled.   *Strain into a coupe glass.

*Garnish

Spiked Rose lemonade anyone? Let’s just say @belvoirfarm_usa is my absolute go to for luxury syrups and craft mixers! Grab a bottle and thank me later .
